description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an opening in the multidisciplinary Stem Cell Transplantation team here at the Bristol Haematology and Oncology Centre, for a motivated and efficient nurse with a strong clinical background in haematology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The successful applicant will support our two band 7 Clinical Nurse Specialists managing the coordination of the regional stem cell transplantation (SCT) service and national immune effector cells (IEC) programme, providing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; specialist nursing advice and care to patients and families along the SCT and IEC pathway. Equal importance to this role is the management and coordination of donors.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will be actively involved in education, audit and research, constantly looking for ways to improve the service for patients, their families, and staff. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a full time role, with the expectation to cover Monday to Friday. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Claire Stokes - Clinical Nurse Specialist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Claire.Stokes@UHBW.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 0117 342 1118&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Maria Mazza-Beange, Clinical Nurse Specialists, Stem Cell Transplantation&lt;/p&gt;
